From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 18:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Add default-disabled GRX Route B rd_native fused_post_chain
 in-frame fusion-first replacement

Stacked on 0001..0029 + 0040 + 0041 + 0042 + 0043 + 0044 (the branch-HEAD
gpu_culling tail plus the tonemap, ssao_blur, taa_resolve, particles_copy and
cluster_store rd_native slices). Sixth Route B replacement slice and the
FUSION-FIRST leg of the two-level fallback: fused rd_native -> single-pass
tonemap rd_native (patch 0040) -> native Godot tonemap chain. SELF-CONTAINED on
the culling tail (the fused shim scaffold 0036-0038 is on the mutually-exclusive
fused tail and is NOT in this stack).

- drivers/d3d12/d3d12_hooks.h: new default-false virtual
  try_record_fused_post_chain_rd_native(RID src_color, RID lum_source,
  RID prev_luminance, RID dst_color, RID dst_luminance, Size2i, Size2i, f32, f32,
  f32, f32, f32, f32, f32, f32). Base returns false.
- modules/rurix_accel/register_types.cpp: two new default-safe settings
  (.../passes/fused_post_chain/backend int default 0 and .../rd_container_path).
- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.{h,cpp}: try_record_fused_post_chain_rd_native
  override + its own 64-byte b0 / 5-resource constants.
- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp: the fusion-first
  gate runs before the patch 0040 tonemap rd_native gate.

In-place revision #1 (Design 1 shadow-recompute, unlocked by the patch 0048
Luminance-API getters; no number change): the call site now supplies THREE
DISTINCT luminance buffers via luminance->get_current_luminance_buffer /
get_previous_luminance_buffer / get_luminance_reduce_penultimate_buffer
(lum_source = current SRV t1, prev_luminance = previous SRV t2, and a valid
distinct dst_luminance handle = penultimate). The module binds the two distinct
luminance SRVs but REDIRECTS the fused kernel's dst_luminance UAV (u1) to a
self-owned 1x1 R32_SFLOAT STORAGE scratch that is NEVER read back, so no real
luminance buffer is written (writing current would corrupt the auto-exposure
feedback; writing penultimate would corrupt next frame's reduction source). The
gate is ALSO ANDed with the shared rurix_tonemap_linear_subset_compatible
predicate from patch 0040 (LINEAR + convert_to_srgb + no color effects; auto
exposure is allowed here because the fused kernel folds the luminance step in).

In-place revision #2 (GRX-019 real auto-exposure parameter pipeline; no number
change): the fused hook signature is extended with FIVE trailing floats
(p_min_luminance, p_max_luminance, p_exposure_adjust, p_first_frame,
p_auto_exposure_scale) and the module packs the REAL per-frame values into b0
dwords 8-15, replacing the earlier placeholder scalars (max=1/min=0/adjust=1/
first_frame=0/scale=1) that caused the measured max_abs=85/mean_abs=66 rd_native
parity gap. The values are the exact arguments the native luminance_reduction +
tonemap consume: auto_exposure_max/min_sensitivity, the adjust step, the
set_immediate (first-frame) flag, and camera_attributes_get_auto_exposure_scale.
The call site hoists function-scope copies of the four reduce parameters (next to
the existing function-scope auto_exposure_scale) and assigns them inside the
auto-exposure block; safe defaults are used when auto-exposure is inactive (they
never reach the kernel because the distinct-luminance guard fails closed). NO b0
layout / DXIL / RTS0 / container change — dwords 8-15 already carried these
fields; only the packed runtime values change.

HONEST BOUNDARY (recorded in the manifest / PASS_CONTRACT): this is a
shadow-recompute — the native luminance_reduction still runs in FULL, the net
dispatch saving is ZERO, and NO structural fusion / dispatch saving is claimed
(engaged / shadow-luminance-write / dispatch-savings-not-claimed). Only the
LINEAR + convert_to_srgb tonemap leg (t0 -> u0) is the real replacement. A true
fusion (Design 2: glow-off gate + skip the native final level + external SWAP)
is a later batch. Fails closed (cascades to tonemap rd_native) when auto-exposure
did not produce distinct current/previous luminance buffers.

Fail-closed everywhere: default backend == 0 keeps the tonemap rd_native /
native chain. RXGD_ABI_VERSION unchanged (no C ABI struct change, no
RxGdCaps.flags bit; bridge-independent). No performance claim is made.
